28/06/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- One person died at the weekend amid severe flooding caused by torrential rains that forced hundreds of evacuations, mainly in the eastern and northern regions, authorities announced on Sunday (June 27th). The latest victim died in the Vrancea region. Another person is missing in Bacau County. Last week, three people died in central Romania. (AFP, Mediafax, Financiarul, Hotnews.ro, Jurnalul National, Adevarul - 27/06/10)
